    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-07-10T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-07-10T00:00:00-05:00" n="1006"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1006">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">711.94114A/361: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Minister in Switzerland</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Harrison</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-07-10">July 10,
                            1944</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>2362. American Interests, Far East. Reference Legation’s 1288, March 3. Inquire
                    of Gorgé whether there has been any improvement in facility with which civilian
                    internees and prisoners of war may send and receive letters. Also inquire
                    whether Gorgé has yet received any communications from prisoners of war or
                    civilian internees.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
                <postscript>
                    <p>[For statement by the Department of State on the number of American civilians
                        held in Japanese custody as of July 12, see bracketed note, <ref
                            target="#pg_1043">page 1043</ref>.]</p>
                </postscript>
            </div>
        </body>
